Mr. Audet is not worried about seeing the number of clients fluctuating like this.
For me, this is not an indication of a change in trend, he observed.
It varies from quarter to quarter with a very strong competition.
Horse in beef products
Horse meat was detected in canned beef-based products, sold by two small, low-price British distribution brands, today announced the Agency for Food Hygiene.
Regular tests revealed that the products, developed in January in Romania and sold by the Home Bargains and Quality Save chains, contained horse DNA of 1 to 5%.
