At least one group of online hacktivists claimed to be responsible for the failure of the NSA site by a DSD attack.
The DSD attacks aim to flood a targeted site until the servers are overburdened and the site collapses.
Cyber tactics are not very sophisticated and attacks are not intended to enter the internal network of the targeted system.
The NSA once ultra secret, a time nicknamed the "No Search Agency", has been under fire from the projectors and strongly criticized in recent months following a wave of revelations about its extensive communications surveillance programs at the national level and abroad – which are part of the NSA's secret files stolen from the agency and disclosed by the former disfellowshiped consultant Edward Snowden.
This growing controversy around the agency has led to many speculations that tonight's incident was the result of a targeted cyber-operation.
