We believe Bombardier will record new orders for its CSeries aircraft as the flight trial program progresses.
However, if no new orders are announced in the coming months, we expect the market to become more skeptical about the program.
Bombardier hopes that the CSeries aircraft family will be able to catapult it into the lower segment of a market today dominated by Boeing and Airbus.
The first test aircraft was unveiled in March and flew out for the first time in September after months of delay.
But the number of firm orders for CSeries aircraft has so far been modest to 177. It appears that potential buyers are awaiting the results of flight tests to validate the company's assertions regarding the energy efficiency and potential savings of the new line aircraft.
