Last month, Mark Rosenker of the National Transportation Safety Board, a national transport safety expert on CBS News, said mobile phones were still considered risky.
"Mobile phones are really a problem, not only because they could possibly create interference with navigational instruments, but because we know, according to the CCF, that they could disrupt mobile phone relays if they are used on board," said Rosenker.
